The warden hoist a large piece of metal that would be the replacement
for that huge hole in the side of the bridge.  From the inside the
captain began to attach it with a welding torch, from the outside:
Betaspiel (who is the only one between the three of them that actually
had any ship repair experience, began welding it to the outside.  Once
it was in place, they got a soldering tool and sealed all the cracks
in the armor.  They then took a break.

The sun beat down, making all the metal click a little as it expanded.
 The warden went back inside to check on his inmates.  Betaspeil
climbed to the top of the ship to see what could be seen from there. 
The ship was situated about 15 klicks east from the edge of this
desert which surrounded the ship on all sides.  Nobody from the ship
had actually left to investigate what was over there, they had been
too busy trying to stay alive after the prison break.

After their brief rest break, Tigon grabbed one of his prisoners who
had some electrical training and set him with the captain to work in
the bridge.  Betaspeil and Tigon escorted another prisoner outside
where they had him paint the newly patched hull.  Tigon guarded the
prisoner, and Beta examined one of the ship&#39;s defensive cannons on the
lower side of the hull, it had been shot out in an earlier exchange
with a prisoner and it needed to be completely overhauled.  He
unhooked it from the ship and brought it into the cargo room.  Tigon&#39;s
prisoner finished his painting job and was put back in his cell.

The captain seemed pleased with his captive&#39;s work.  He leaned on a
wall, as the prisoner put the finishing touches on one of the control
panels that had been shot up.  After the work was done, he was
rewarded with a trip to the CR chamber, then he was put back in his
cell.

It was a good day of work, but they still had lots to do...

